<h1 class="Part">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Part-I">Part I.</a> The Rules
</h1>
<h1 class="Chapter">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Chapter-1">1</a> How To Play
</h1>
<div class="Unindented">
This game is not designed or aimed at novice GMs. It is my own notes on a setting I have used with my play group. Shared in a way that I hope other people may enjoy.
</div>
<div class="Indented">
Cops; the muscular line between law and chaos. The boys in blue protect the city from the normal day to day criminals, busting heads and taking no prisoners<span class="Marginal">
Actually they do take prisoners. That’s the point.
</span>
.
</div>
<h2 class="Section">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Section-1.1">1.1</a> GM Agenda
</h2>
<div class="Unindented">
Why are you running the game?<span class="Marginal">
Pick your own reasons.
</span>

</div>
<ul>
<li>
Make the characters’ lives’ not boring.
</li>
<li>
To explore a mystery together.
</li>

</ul>
<h2 class="Section">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Section-1.2">1.2</a> Character Statistics
</h2>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Physical</b> Strength, dexterity it’s all here. 
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Resilience</b> Physical toughness.Take a lickin’ and keep on tickin’. 
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Wits</b> Cleverness and sense. 
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Guts</b> Hunches, confidence.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Presence</b> Personality. Persuasion, intimidation and cajoling.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Weird</b> Connection to The Dark. This also is a measure of the Dark’s connection to the character.<div class="vspace" style="height: defskip*;">

</div>

</div>
<div class="Unindented">
Cops are tough, clever and attuned to the world around them. To begin with you get one +3 bonus, two +2 bonuses and two +1 bonuses. Put them where you like. Most of the moves can be used in various ways. Want to dominate a room with your muscular presence buff your Physical, want to dominate a room by standing very, very still then buff your Presence. Play the way you want.
</div>
<h2 class="Section">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Section-1.3">1.3</a> Wounds &amp; Damage
</h2>
<div class="Unindented">
You’re going to get hurt. Probably going to get hurt a lot. Wound levels are affected by Resilience. For every bonus point in Resilience you get an extra level os Still Tickin’.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Uninjured</b> Nothing has happened to you. You’re fine. Be careful
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Still</b> <b>Tickin’</b> Someone has managed to lay a hit on you. No game effect.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Wounded</b> You’re hit and have taken some serious damage. Suffer a -1 to any Move.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Grevious</b> You’re probably bleeding and covered in bruises. Suffer a -3 to any move.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>Unconscious</b> Yep. You’re lying on the floor. You can’t do anything. Unless you’re in the Dreamlands.
</div>
<div class="Labeling">
<b>At</b> <b>Death’s</b> <b>Door</b> Without trained help you’re going to die, or worse.
</div>
<div class="Unindented">
Some weapons do damage that last. Firearms for example do damage that lasts between scenes unless specifically healed in game. Lesser damage, from a bar fight for example, does not last between scenes. Even if it left you lying on the floor unconscious.
</div>
<h2 class="Section">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Section-1.4">1.4</a> Universal Moves
</h2>
<h1 class="Chapter">
<a class="toc" name="toc-Chapter-2">2</a> Character Classes Cops 
</h1>
<blockquote class="Quotation">
"I’m gonna come down on you so hard your going to have to reach up to tie your shoe laces." - The Sweeney
</blockquote>
<div class="Unindented">
<span class="TODO">Should I combine all the cops into one?</span>
</div>
<div class="Indented">
All the cops should be fairly tough, able to hold their own in a fistfight, have basic firearms training and have a solid grounding in crime scene investigation. Every character has to be working for the police in some capacity. Every character also has to be either human, originally human or at the very least mostly human.<span class="Marginal">
You can change this at will.
</span>

</div>
